{"id": "EUVD-2022-54986", "enisaUuid": "b88af0e8-d7ba-3bba-8ed3-bd61668bd0f5", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: mediatek: mt8195: Fix error handling in mt8195_mt6359_rt1019_rt5682_dev_probe\n\nThe device_node pointer is returned by of_parse_phandle()  with refcount\nincremented. We should use of_node_put() on it when done.\n\nThis function only calls of_node_put() in the regular path.\nAnd it will cause refcount leak in error path.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T01:56:02", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:47:02", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c652f8f0875b569f8afa80b8cf9762828fd6187b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c4b7174fe5bb875a09a78674a14a1589d1a672f3", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49240"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49240"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0cadfc00-2a64-3afe-94b6-032fa77a1844", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.17"}, {"id": "3acfaac5-3fb4-3151-8fde-83e73afc750a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.2"}, {"id": "89c9ae5f-7d44-3e92-9e73-8f4645603985", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "cb11e570-fcbb-322c-bc97-772e277857fe", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18"}, {"id": "d8fe1574-849a-32d5-91e9-0db43769dc3d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "082482a5022780d42180a394fe6843e71fe963d8 <c652f8f0875b569f8afa80b8cf9762828fd6187b"}, {"id": "e2dc3dbd-a5e6-38e4-ba77-32eeff42132b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "082482a5022780d42180a394fe6843e71fe963d8 <c4b7174fe5bb875a09a78674a14a1589d1a672f3"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "9d587dca-6211-3cf7-a462-315b53da61a9", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}